Repository Name Unauthorized: Library of Congress Prints & Photographs Division
Notes: Unique in their scope and richness, the picture  collections number more than 14 million images. These include  photographs, historical prints, posters, cartoons, documentary drawings, fine  prints, and architectural and engineering designs. While international in  scope, the collections are particularly strong in materials documenting the history of the United States and the lives, interests, and achievements of the  American people.
